        <profileDesc>
            <abstract>
                <p>
                    “Gloss” refers to a note aimed to solve a purely language difficulty, in particular adding clarifications to difficult words 
                    (frequently just single words, synonyms, in Amharic or Geez, or sometimes longer passages).
                </p>
                <p>Examples are:
                    <list>
                        <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESdd040"/>, f. 5r.</p>
                  </item>
                        <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESdd005"/>, f. 2r.</p>
                  </item>
                    </list>
            </p>
            </abstract>
